<Author>Iffy50
<Content>Not too bad I've actually stayed in this hotel for more than 2 months if you count everything over the last 8 years. Generally this hotel is pretty decent, but only on a relative scale. I stayed here for work and the room prices were always negociated, often significantly.The rooms are clean. The showers work acceptably, but they don't have an actual door, they just have a divider which leads to water on the floor. It's manageable. The drains are slow in every room I've stayed in (6 different ones or so). Again, it's manageable.The best thing about this hotel is that there is a train stop within a 3 minute walk. Take this to go downtown. It's smooth and easy.I recommend a short drive to the nearby mall if you want somewhere quick to eat. (Eroski is the name of the mall) There are some good options there. Service in the hotel restaurant is horrible and everything is very expensive. If you are going to eat, eat at the bar. It's faster and the food is fine. The only downside is that you won't be able to eat at an actual table. Be warned, the drinks cost a fortune.  The high speed internet is hit or miss. Depending on your room location it can work well or not at all. The internet is via 1 hour or 24 hour access cards. The one hour is 7.5 Euro? 24 hour= 12 Euro? (very close to that range anyway) 
