<Author>PDH01
<Content>Truly uninspiring hotel and location Novotel has a monopoly in its out-of-the way industrial park, which is clear in both prices and what you get.In spite of being new-ish the hotel feels faded. The rooms are ok sized, but nothing special and the stench of cigarettes can be overpowering even for people who smoke themselves. The service all depends on who you talk to and their mode. The service has been both exceptional and otherwise. The food should simply be avoided.Two issues:Location-wise, note that it is often difficult to get a cab in evening, so you might have to wait for an hour or more. The wifi is unreliable, and if you get a connection depends on where yr room is located.I've stayed here a number of times with work, but not since I found San Cugat Hotel and Restaurant in nearby San Cougat proper. 
