<Author>American_in_Italy
<Content>Basic, and stranded without a car I stayed at the novotel for 4 nights, and it was basically what I expected, maybe a little worse. The good parts:Room was fairly large, clean (but could use updates), and the staff were friendly / competent. It was quiet.The bad parts: being in an industrial park near the highway, I did not feel like I could walk anywhere so I was forced 2 nights for their room service, which literally had TWO choices. Choice one (ham) and choice two (spanish omelet). I also did not like the room set up in that I ran my toe into the sofa sleeper next to the bed (which I never used) until I got smart and wrapped a towel around the metal leg (which the maid removed every day so I had to start over.) They did offer high speed internet, but at 9Euro an hour I decided to do dial up. The shower sprayer never stayed in position so I had to shower with my body almost glued to the shower wall. Ugh. I would stay at the Sant Cugat H  R next time, but it was full. 
